When Draymond can lead the league w/ 2.03 spg in 2017 and Davis w/ 2.57 bpg in 2018 (both all-time lows), something's just not right on the defensive end. Though the league average for offensive rebounds have also been at an all-time low in recent years.

snippet.textDisplay: The triple double era vs era thing. Think of back in the early decade of NBA basketball, rebounds were nothing, just common currency, because teams were trigger-happy like crazy.
